  "prompt": "How much cubic meter of cement, sand required for 12mm cement sand plaster 1:6 for 950 sq m?",
  "response": "To calculate the amount of cement and sand required for a 12mm thick cement-sand plaster in a 1:6 ratio for an area of 950 square meters, follow these steps:\n\n### Step 1: Calculate the Volume of Plaster\nFirst, determine the volume of plaster needed. The thickness is 12mm, which is \\(0.012\\) meters.\n\n\\[\n\\text{Volume} = \\text{Area} \\times \\text{Thickness}\n\\]\n\\[\n\\text{Volume} = 950 \\, \\text{m}^2 \\times 0.012 \\, \\text{m} = 11.4 \\, \\text{m}^3\n\\]\n\n### Step 2: Calculate the Total Mix Proportion\nThe mix ratio is 1:6 (cement:sand). The total parts in the mix are:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Total Parts} = 1 + 6 = 7\n\\]\n\n### Step 3: Calculate the Volume of Cement\nCement occupies \\(1/7\\) of the total mix volume:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Volume of Cement} = \\frac{1}{7} \\times 11.4 \\, \\text{m}^3 \\approx 1.63 \\, \\text{m}^3\n\\]\n\n### Step 4: Calculate the Volume of Sand\nSand occupies \\(6/7\\) of the total mix volume:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Volume of Sand} = \\frac{6}{7} \\times 11.4 \\, \\text{m}^3 \\approx 9.77 \\, \\text{m}^3\n\\]\n\n### Step 5: Convert Volume to Weight (Optional)\nIf you need the weight of cement:\n- The density of cement is approximately \\(1440 \\, \\text{kg/m}^3\\).\n\\[\n\\text{Weight of Cement} = 1.63 \\, \\text{m}^3 \\times 1440 \\, \\text{kg/m}^3 \\approx 2347 \\, \\text{kg}\n\\]\n\n### Summary of Materials:\n- **Cement:** \\(1.63 \\, \\text{m}^3\\) (or approximately \\(2347 \\, \\text{kg}\\))\n- **Sand:** \\(9.77 \\, \\text{m}^3\\)\n\nThese calculations provide the required volumes of cement and sand for the plastering job. Adjustments might be necessary based on site conditions and material characteristics.",
